.TH "NAVIGATOR.DEVICEMEMORY" "3JS" "January 27, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Navigator.deviceMemory \- Navigator: deviceMemory property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]deviceMemory\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]Navigator\f[R] interface returns the approximate amount of device
memory in gigabytes.
.PP
The reported value is imprecise to curtail fingerprinting.
It\(cqs approximated by rounding the actual memory to the nearest power
of 2, then dividing that number by 1024.
It is then clamped within lower and upper bounds to protect the privacy
of owners of very low\-memory or high\-memory devices.
These bounds may change over time (see browser compatibility table).
.SH VALUE
A floating point number coarsened to a power of two value, clamped to
implement\-defined limits.
.PP
For example, if a browser does not report below \f[CR]2\f[R] or above
\f[CR]32\f[R] then the value is one of: \f[CR]2\f[R], \f[CR]4\f[R],
\f[CR]8\f[R], \f[CR]16\f[R], \f[CR]32\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] memory = navigator.deviceMemory;
console.log(\(gaThis device approximately ${memory}GiB of RAM.\(ga);
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Sec\-CH\-Device\-Memory\f[R] HTTP header
